      "writtenOn": "2015-10-16T01:30:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "what about a vector of pairs and an undordered_map of \u003ckey -\u003e index in vector\u003e ? you can do both lookup in O(1) and get by index that way; also, as you never insert in the middle after loading there\u0027s no danger of screwing things up\n\nWell, comments complicate things a bit\nwhat would be better here is:\n\nvector\u003cpair\u003ckey, value\u003e\u003e for everything\nunordered_map\u003ckey, index in first vector\u003e\u003e for an access by key\nunordered_map\u003cindex of the key-value, index in first vector\u003e for access by index\n\nOr some other ways\nIn the end you will always just dump out the first vector as a new file content",
      "range": {
